data.description: Welcome to Blue Spruce Drive, tucked away in The Pines, one of Dewitt's most desired and mature neighborhoods. This move-in ready and completely updated 3,200 square foot house features over $100,000 of recent renovations including a new, custom designed and installed kitchen by K. Fedewa Builders, flooring, paint, updated bathrooms, stair railings, front porch and backyard landscaping. The 3-bedroom house includes two full bathrooms, two half-bathrooms, two gas fireplaces, two living areas, updated windows in the main living area, and a large open basement offering plenty of storage or potential living or workspace. Enter through the front door and the large foyer opens to the second-floor new black spindle stair railings and chandelier. Double French doors lead to a private office which features floor to ceiling refinished white cabinets and shiplap, a private and beautiful view of the mature front yard pine trees - perfect for working from home, crafting or a man cave. From the foyer you'll enter an open living room with tall, cathedral ceilings, updated windows that allow plenty of natural light and access to a peaceful three-seasons room with original pine-knotted walls. The new kitchen includes a large island with plenty of storage, white cabinets, lighting and gorgeous white quartz countertops. The kitchen flows to a large open dining area which includes three updated floor to ceiling bay windows. The first-floor laundry room and updated half-bathroom are located off the kitchen, through the mudroom that leads to the two-car garage with tall ceilings, providing plenty of additional storage. Enjoy the convenience of the large, main-level primary bedroom which includes a beautiful black and white tile gas fireplace, a large walk-in closet and an updated, private bathroom featuring a double sink and new flooring, lighting, fixtures and shower door. In the living room you will admire the new stair railing of black spindles that leads you to the second floor living room and two additional large bedrooms, including a massive walk-in closet that could be utilized as another room. The updated second-floor bathroom includes beautiful tile surrounding the shower. Enjoy bird and wildlife watching from your quiet backyard, which was professionally seeded in 2022. A large back deck offers plenty of entertainment space and conveniently wraps around to the front of the house. The neighborhood is located across from a Looking Glass River access site and park, connects to Padgett Park trails and is within walking distance to the dog park, shopping, dining, the Dewitt library and Schavey Road Elementary. Book your private showing now!
